 case of <i>currach</i> ‘wet plain, marsh’.","Scottish: habitational name from Corrie in Dumfriesshire or another place so named (see   Corrie  ).","Scottish form of Irish   Curry   or, in Arran, an Anglicized form of <b>Mac Mhuirich</b> (see   McMurray  )."]}]},{"name":"Lydia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Greek origin, meaning ‘woman from Lydia’, an area of Asia Minor. The name is borne in the Bible by a woman of Thyatira who was converted by St Paul and who entertained him in her house (Acts 16:14–15, 40). It has enjoyed steady popularity in the English-speaking world since the 17th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Lydia Corrie was born in 1400, in Ayrshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 son with Sir William Corrie. She died in 1460, in Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1400–1460":"1400–1460","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1425":"1425","1400":"1400","1460":"1460","1504":"1504","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1400–1460":"1400–1460","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1425":"1425","1400":"1400","1460":"1460","1504":"1504","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1400–1460":"1400–1460","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1425":"1425","1400":"1400","1460":"1460","1504":"1504","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Écosse","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lady Lydia Corrie est née en 1400, à Ayrshire, Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir William Corrie. Elle est décédée en 1460, à Ayr, Ayrshire, Écosse, à l’âge de 60 ans."},"de":{"1400–1460":"1400–1460","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1425":"1425","1400":"1400","1460":"1460","1504":"1504","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Lady Lydia Corrie wurde 1400 in Ayrshire, Scotland geboren. Sie hatte mit S